cked": false, "assignee": null, "assignees": [], "milestone": null, "comments": 2, "created_at": "2018-11-01T16:41:12Z", "updated_at": "2021-03-08T15:51:02Z", "closed_at": null, "author_association": "MEMBER", "active_lock_reason": null, "body": "I think we had that discussion at some point but I do not think we have an explicit issue.  I think that API should become a bit more \"symmetric\".  We already can `drop` what we `get`, `remove` what we `add`, and IMHO we should be able to `uninstall` what we `install`.  But that is not the case ATM with top level datasets:\r\n\r\n```shell\r\n$> datalad install https://github.com/OpenNeuroDatasets/ds001499\r\n[INFO   ] Cloning https://github.com/OpenNeuroDatasets/ds001499 [1 other candidates] into '/mnt/btrfs/scrap/tmp/openneuro/ds001499' \r\ninstall(ok): /mnt/btrfs/scrap/tmp/openneuro/ds001499 (dataset)\r\n\r\n$> datalad uninstall ds001499 \r\nuninstall(error): /mnt/btrfs/scrap/tmp/openneuro/ds001499 (dataset) [will not uninstall top-level dataset (consider `remove` command)]\r\n```\r\nand I cannot recall the original motivation for having it so (IIRC it was very much intentional).", "closed_by": null, "reactions": {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/datalad/datalad/issues/2967/reactions", "total_count": 0, "+1": 0, "-1": 0, "laugh": 0, "hooray": 0, "confused": 0, "heart": 0, "rocket": 0, "eyes": 0}, "timeline_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/datalad/datalad/issues/2967/timeline", "performed_via_github_app": null}